<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880822-0052 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Vishay Intertechnology Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> VSH </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Vishay Intertechnology Inc. said it began a tender offer to acquire all of Sfernice, Society Francaise d'Electro-Resistance, for about 405 million francs (US$63 million).    Vishay, a Malvern, Pa.-based maker of precision resistors and stress-measurement devices, had proposed in June to acquire a 67% stake in the French maker of electronic resistors. At the time, Vishay said it would expand its offer to cover all shares if it could arrange additional financing.    According to terms, Vishay will pay 848 francs a share for all shares outstanding, and will also pay 100 francs for each of Sfernice's warrants outstanding. Sfernice holders also will be offered the option of exchanging one Sfernice share for two Vishay shares plus 468 francs. </TEXT></DOC>